1
00:00:00,490 --> 00:00:04,520
[Never Too Late]

2
00:00:05,400 --> 00:00:06,710
Ding Ran.

3
00:00:06,710 --> 00:00:09,700
[Episode 4]

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,300
Don't you see what time it is? Aren't you working today?

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,100
Ding Ran.

6
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,100
Ding Ran!

7
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:35,300
When did this brat leave?

8
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,500
Jiang Xile, wrong way.

9
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,100
This way.

10
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,300
This teargraphy examination—
[Mammography Examination Room]

11
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,200
Mammography.

12
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:21,800
What's mammography?

13
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:23,600
It's a type of X-ray examination.

14
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:26,700
It's a little special, but there's no need to worry too much.

15
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,600
How special?

16
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:31,100
You need to undress and raise your breasts…

17
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:35,500
Raise? How to raise them?

18
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,700
Like this. Raise them.

19
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:41,900
And then the machine will press down.

20
00:01:47,900 --> 00:01:51,400
If I raise them, can it press them down?

21
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:54,000
You're overestimating me.

22
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:08,800
What's wrong?

23
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,500
Don't talk to me for now.

24
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:13,000
It's too embarrassing.

25
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Slow down. Don't fall again.

26
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,400
Eat more.

27
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,800
Xile went to team building.

28
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,100
Xiao Ran doesn't have time to come home for dinner.

29
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:29,600
They're suddenly not at home. There's no one arguing.

30
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:34,500
Our home, which was finally lively, suddenly became quiet again.

31
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:38,900
Fortunately, there's you to eat the food I cooked.

32
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:43,500
Didn't Xiao Ran eat the food you cooked before?

33
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:46,100
To tell you the truth, before you moved in,

34
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:50,700
the number of times Xiao Ran ate at home in a year didn't exceed this number.

35
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:54,500
He likes to plan all things in life.

36
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:57,900
Even these five meals were all scheduled in advance.

37
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:01,600
Sometimes I wonder, will he suddenly come home for dinner today

38
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:04,100
and catch me off guard?

39
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:09,000
Or maybe he will suddenly bring a girlfriend home and surprise me.

40
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:14,220
But it never happened.

41
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,500
Very boring.

42
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:23,100
What kind of girl does Xiao Ran like?

43
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,400
As you said,

44
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:35,700
it seems that I've never seen Xiao Ran like any girl.

45
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:40,300
It can't be that he doesn't dislike girls.

46
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,100
Still not sleeping?

47
00:04:00,100 --> 00:04:02,000
I can't sleep.

48
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:12,300
♫ I'm alone in my room, reminiscing about the past ♫

49
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:13,700
Here.

50
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:15,900
When did you prepare this?

51
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:20,600
If you still can't sleep, there's melatonin and earplugs inside.

52
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,800
How do you know I need these?

53
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:27,400
It's your first time staying in the hospital. I figured you'd need them.

54
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:32,600
♫ All these years, we cried and laughed ♫

55
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,800
Here. Let me help you put them on.

56
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,400
Okay.

57
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,300
♫ Time encourages changes ♫

58
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:45,200
♫ A heart shattered in regrets is hard to mend ♫

59
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:51,000
♫ It may take several more years to forget those years ♫

60
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,300
Still not sleeping?

61
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:55,100
But I still can't sleep.

62
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:58,000
How can you sleep with your eyes open?

63
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,700
Go to sleep. You're having surgery tomorrow.

64
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,600
See you tomorrow.

65
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,700
Good night.

66
00:05:08,700 --> 00:05:10,300
Good night.

67
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:23,600
Young lady, you've changed a boyfriend?

68
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,300
You have good taste.

69
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:27,400
It's good to be with a doctor.

70
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,700
Don't listen to her.

71
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,200
The one from a few days ago is more reliable.

72
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,700
He's a safe option.

73
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:38,000
When looking for a boyfriend, you have to find a reliable one, not a handsome one.

74
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,300
- What do you know?
- What do you know?

75
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:42,900
- How good is it to be with a doctor?
- Okay, okay. I don't want to argue with you.

76
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:45,400
I don't want to argue with you, either.

77
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,300
You're here.

78
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,700
Sit down first.

79
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,500
What's wrong?

80
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,200
Here.

81
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:13,400
Why are you giving me socks?

82
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:16,500
The surgery time is short, but you'll be undressed and lying barefoot.

83
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,500
Your feet might be cold.

84
00:06:19,300 --> 00:06:20,500
Thanks.

85
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:23,000
- Put them on.
- Okay.

86
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,600
They're quite cute.

87
00:06:36,999 --> 00:06:38,736
By the way...

88
00:06:38,736 --> 00:06:40,260
For you.

89
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,200
What is it?

90
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:45,400
Can you play this song for me when you perform the surgery?

91
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:48,000
I feel very calm when I listen to it.

92
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:53,000
After you're fully anaesthetized, you won't hear anything.

93
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:56,900
All right.

94
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,500
Let's go.

95
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,500
Get ready for the surgery.

96
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,800
Sponge.

97
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:27,800
♫ When it's late at night, I feel powerless ♫

98
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:30,700
Xiao Ting, help me play that song.

99
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:34,400
- Okay, Dr. Ding.
- It's my first time seeing you listen to a song while performing surgery.

100
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:38,200
♫ The blurry darkness from day to night ♫

101
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:43,600
♫ Seems like my only safe haven ♫

102
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:50,600
♫ The rain, like my tears, quietly seeps into my soul ♫

103
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,500
Ding Ran!

104
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:56,600
Wait for me. I'll go with you.

105
00:07:58,500 --> 00:08:03,000
♫ The most perfect summer and autumn are already yesterday ♫

106
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,400
Ding Ran.

107
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:06,500
♫ That figure has disappeared from the window ♫

108
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:08,200
What?

109
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,000
Nothing, I just want to call you.

110
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
♫ I wish I could return to that year ♫

111
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:20,200
♫ In the blink of an eye, several years have passed since summer and autumn ♫

112
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:23,500
Ding Ran, where's your new bike?

113
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:25,500
It's broken.

114
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:28,100
- I'll give you a ride then.
- Thanks, no need.

115
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:29,400
Why not?

116
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:32,200
A girl giving a guy a ride is not embarrassing.

117
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,200
Jiang Xile.

118
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,000
Jiang Xile.

119
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,800
Jiang Xile.

120
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,700
Wake up.

121
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,400
Jiang Xile.

122
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:57,400
Jiang Xile.

123
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:04,100
Has the surgery not started yet?

124
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,700
It's already over. I didn't lie to you, did I?

125
00:09:07,700 --> 00:09:11,000
It was very quick. Nothing happened.

126
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,000
My breasts are gone.

127
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,800
It's the anesthesia that hasn't worn off.

128
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:29,200
This feels so strange.

129
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:38,600
Don't touch your wound.

130
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:52,400
- The phone is ringing.
- I'll help you.

131
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,700
Who is it?
[666]

132
00:09:55,700 --> 00:09:57,800
Who is 666?

133
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:00,600
Hello.

134
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:02,680
Ding Ran?

135
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:05,660
Which ward is Jiang Xile in? I'm coming over now.

136
00:10:05,660 --> 00:10:07,260
Okay, I'll be right there.

137
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:08,804
Okay.

138
00:10:15,979 --> 00:10:17,659
Liuliu.

139
00:10:24,339 --> 00:10:25,820
Liuliu, it's really you.

140
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:27,680
Qi Fei, what a coincidence.

141
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,120
I finally found you.

142
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,360
Why are you here? I couldn't find you in your store.

143
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:33,780
You didn't reply to my messages, nor did you answer my calls.

144
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:35,960
Are you… are you sick?

145
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,279
No, no.

146
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:38,940
I was too busy recently.

147
00:10:38,940 --> 00:10:42,219
I finally got some time to visit my hospitalized friend.

148
00:10:42,219 --> 00:10:45,680
Why are you also in the hospital? Are you sick?

149
00:10:49,379 --> 00:10:53,199
Look, the heart you drew for me is still here.

150
00:10:53,199 --> 00:10:55,420
What an innocent young boy.

151
00:10:55,420 --> 00:10:58,039
He even fell for that lie.

152
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,859
My skateboard.

153
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:34,460
- Don't play with your skateboard in the hospital next time, okay?
- Got it. Thank you, Brother.

154
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:36,200
Be careful.

155
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,580
Liuliu, what did you just say?

156
00:11:39,580 --> 00:11:43,400
I said my heart was also here.

157
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,859
So you didn't wipe it off, either.

158
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:02,700
Qi Fei, your coat is still at my place.

159
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,380
Do you want to come over and get it?

160
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:07,820
By the way, have a cup of tea.

161
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:29,899
Don't touch your wound.

162
00:12:36,059 --> 00:12:39,400
Why is he suddenly so concerned about me?

163
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:42,340
Is it because I'm his patient?

164
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,779
Annoying.

165
00:12:54,686 --> 00:12:56,608
[666]

166
00:13:04,199 --> 00:13:06,220
What's going on?

167
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:13,320
Baby.

168
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:15,179
Liuliu, what are you doing?

169
00:13:15,179 --> 00:13:18,119
Why are you calling me at this time?

170
00:13:18,119 --> 00:13:21,340
I can't sleep. I want to chat with you.

171
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:23,440
Baby, if you can't sleep, you should count sheep.

172
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,379
That way you'll fall asleep quickly.

173
00:13:25,379 --> 00:13:27,760
Counting sheep doesn't work.

174
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:29,360
Who is it?

175
00:13:29,999 --> 00:13:31,739
My mom.

176
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:35,240
Hello?

177
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:39,060
How did I become your mom?

178
00:13:44,560 --> 00:13:47,280
Lu Liuliu, you are really…

179
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:49,919
Even calling me mom.

180
00:13:50,641 --> 00:13:51,963
[Ms. Xiao]

181
00:13:56,099 --> 00:13:57,839
My mom.

182
00:14:00,609 --> 00:14:01,966
[Ms. Xiao]

183
00:14:02,580 --> 00:14:04,180
No.

184
00:14:08,059 --> 00:14:11,160
Oh, my God. Oh, God.

185
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:15,039
What should I do?

186
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:23,580
Jiang Xile, where are you going?

187
00:14:23,580 --> 00:14:25,380
My mom wants to video call me.

188
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:26,880
What should I do?

189
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:28,619
Wait.

190
00:14:30,302 --> 00:14:35,039
♫ It seems to have some kind of penetrating power  ♫

191
00:14:35,039 --> 00:14:38,920
You didn't button your shirt well. Your mom will notice.

192
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:42,159
Thank you. I'll call her in the stairwell.

193
00:14:42,159 --> 00:14:46,440
No, the stairwell is too dark. What will you say when your mom asks where you are?

194
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,460
Right, then…

195
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:50,112
Follow me.

196
00:14:51,454 --> 00:14:56,982
♫ It's you who came into my life ♫

197
00:14:56,982 --> 00:15:03,591
♫ Telling me it's easy to find happiness ♫

198
00:15:03,591 --> 00:15:11,051
♫ No one can replace the dream you are in ♫

199
00:15:11,051 --> 00:15:16,076
♫ I'll see you in my dreams till I wake up ♫

200
00:15:28,119 --> 00:15:29,320
Mom.

201
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:31,180
Baby,

202
00:15:31,180 --> 00:15:33,799
why are you outside alone so late?

203
00:15:33,799 --> 00:15:35,800
It's not safe. Where are your colleagues?

204
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,700
My colleagues…

205
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,999
All my colleagues are here.

206
00:15:39,999 --> 00:15:43,380
What are we going to eat later?

207
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:47,840
Xiao Jiang, time for barbecue.

208
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:50,739
Mom, we're going to have barbecue.

209
00:15:50,739 --> 00:15:53,939
Right, we're already there.

210
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:57,739
Boss, give us some skewers.

211
00:16:00,819 --> 00:16:03,039
Don't rush, it's coming.

212
00:16:03,039 --> 00:16:05,659
We're having barbecue, Mom.

213
00:16:15,660 --> 00:16:19,399
Mom, look, why is there suddenly so much smoke in this barbecue restaurant?

214
00:16:19,399 --> 00:16:20,580
It's choking me.

215
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:24,600
Baby, don't eat too much barbecue.

216
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:27,100
- It can make you sick.
- I know, Mom.

217
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:29,200
Come on, cheers!

218
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:32,079
My colleagues are rushing me.

219
00:16:32,079 --> 00:16:35,519
- I won't talk to you for now.
- Okay, bye.

220
00:16:45,019 --> 00:16:47,399
Why are you laughing?

221
00:16:47,399 --> 00:16:51,040
Your Mom calls you baby. My dad calls your mom Baobei.

222
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,880
When I transferred to our high school,

223
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:56,620
I never thought our home would one day become like this.

224
00:16:58,179 --> 00:17:00,200
I didn't expect it, either.

225
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,980
Do you remember when we were Grade Three in high school,

226
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:06,179
we also spent nights like this, looking at the sky.

227
00:17:07,620 --> 00:17:12,619
How is this night different from those nights?

228
00:17:14,092 --> 00:17:16,719
- Jiang Xile.
- Don't worry,

229
00:17:16,719 --> 00:17:19,059
I won't argue with you.

230
00:17:19,059 --> 00:17:21,839
I just suddenly feel

231
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:25,320
being a family with you is quite nice.

232
00:17:31,179 --> 00:17:32,819
Really?

233
00:17:32,819 --> 00:17:34,436
Really.

234
00:17:35,059 --> 00:17:38,759
Let's get along well from today.

235
00:17:44,740 --> 00:17:48,079
Okay, the peace treaty is signed.

236
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:53,179
But since we're going to be family,

237
00:17:53,179 --> 00:17:56,320
there's one thing you must do.

238
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:57,879
What?

239
00:17:57,879 --> 00:18:01,019
My younger brother, call me your elder sister.

240
00:18:01,019 --> 00:18:03,399
Jiang Xile, don't go too far.

241
00:18:03,399 --> 00:18:05,379
- I'm three months older than you.
- Don't let me catch you.

242
00:18:05,379 --> 00:18:06,879
- Wait!
- Call me your elder sister. Call me.

243
00:18:06,879 --> 00:18:09,480
Let me tell you, we were born in the same year. Don't…

244
00:18:09,480 --> 00:18:12,480
But I'm three months older than you.

245
00:18:13,999 --> 00:18:15,980
Don't run around. Be careful of your wound.

246
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:19,960
It's been so many days. It's almost completely healed.

247
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:37,060
What's wrong?

248
00:18:38,039 --> 00:18:40,520
I want to put on my socks,

249
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:45,060
but this bandage is too tight. I can't put them on at all.

250
00:18:47,999 --> 00:18:49,859
What are you doing?

251
00:18:49,859 --> 00:18:53,800
- Let me help you.
- No need, I can do it myself.

252
00:18:55,099 --> 00:19:00,020
Regardless of whether we're going to be a family or not, it's my responsibility to take care of you.

253
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,180
Done.

254
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,839
Did I come at the wrong time?

255
00:19:32,179 --> 00:19:35,279
Liuliu, you finally have time to see me.

256
00:19:35,279 --> 00:19:37,340
Long time no see, Dr. Ding.

257
00:19:37,340 --> 00:19:39,160
Long time no see,

258
00:19:40,456 --> 00:19:42,119
Old Liu.

259
00:19:42,119 --> 00:19:45,259
In this life, I don't want to hear this nickname anymore.

260
00:19:45,259 --> 00:19:48,420
Okay, you two talk. I'll leave.

261
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:49,979
Okay.

262
00:19:49,979 --> 00:19:52,979
- Don't touch your wound.
- I know.

263
00:19:59,099 --> 00:20:01,340
He's quite handsome.

264
00:20:08,919 --> 00:20:12,240
He is smiling. You're also smiling.

265
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:15,780
Something happened between you two.

266
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:18,280
What could happen?

267
00:20:35,780 --> 00:20:40,020
